Good evening Analy and Laguna High School Staff and Families,

We understand this is a stressful time as once again our community is faced with fires and evacuation in areas surrounding Sebastopol.

Under current conditions, Analy and Laguna High Schools will be open for live distance learning instruction starting Monday, August 24th. We will continue to monitor the situation, and will update staff and families if conditions change.

We are sending our thoughts to all of our community that is affected by this fire.

Stay safe,

Toni L Beal, M.A.
Superintendent

post_text:
Hello El Molino Staff and Families,

We understand this is a stressful time as many of our families, staff and greater community are faced with evacuating from their homes due to the Walbridge Fire.

El Molino High School planned to start live instruction via distance learning this coming Monday, August 24th. Due to the current conditions, the District has made a decision to cancel classes for El Molino High School on both Monday and Tuesday, August 24th and 25th.

The current plan is for students to resume school on Wednesday, August 26th with asynchronous learning. On Thursday, August 27th live instruction would resume. We will continue to monitor the situation and provide updates as we move forward.

Our thoughts go out to our community affected by this fire.

Stay safe,
Toni Beal
Superintendent

Toni Beal

post_text: Message from El Molino Principal Matt Dunkle.
shared_text:
El Molino High School
August 18 at 10:25 PM 路

Fire season started early this year. We know that many of you live in evacuation areas, but as of now there appears to be no imminent danger. However, fire can change quickly as weve learned over the recent years.

Please do not worry about school work if you are in an affected area; your safety is our main priority. As always, we are here to help and support our El Molino families. Please do not hesitate to let us know if you need anything to help get through this. Your well being is of paramount concern to us.

Hopefully, this will not escalate and our amazing fire crews will contain this fire before it grows and directly impacts our families, colleagues, students, and our community members.

Like we always do, we will get through this successfully because Together, We are El Molino!

Be Safe!

Matt Dunkle
Principal

As the Employee Appreciation Month of May comes to an end, I would like to share a special message from the Board Trustees and Superintendent thanking our District employees for their dedicated service.

El Mo Ed Fund
May 17 at 8:41 PM 路

El Molino alumnus Michael Valdovinoss wide-ranging career as a psychologist has taken him into war zones and Ivy League classrooms, but the Latino leaders heart has remained in Sonoma County.

The struggles and triumphs he experienced growing up in rural Guerneville as a first-generation Mexican-American shaped his personal and professional life. The 43-year-old, who gives back locally through his work at Santa Rosa Community Health and across the airwaves with a new KBBF radio show, said he aims to empower his community through access to resources and education.

Read more: https://www.pressdemocrat.com/specialsections/hispanicheritage/10946150-181/psychologist-looks-to-improve-access

Sonoma West Times & News honors El Molino graduating senior athlete Sasha Senal 

El Molino senior Sasha Senal made her mark in a stellar, multi-year volleyball career, helping to restore a winning tradition to a storied program. During her four years on the varsity squad, Senal rose to become one of the top outside/middle hitters in the league, posting big numbers of kills and blocks. She was also a respected court leader, serving as a team captain during the Lions run to the North Bay League Redwood Division title last fall.

Read more: http://www.sonomawest.com/sonoma_west_times_and_news/sports/a-tribute-to-graduating-senior-student-athletes/article_aa18265c-9548-11ea-842b-bbcee2bba243.html

post_text:
What a nice surprise for the Analy Seniors in Ag. A special visit from their teacher Heidi Mickelson!
#westcountypride
shared_text:
Heidi Mickelson is with Sebastopol Farmers.
May 14 at 9:51 PM 路

Today I finally got to see some of my (other) kids. It meant a lot to me to hand deliver these packages. Most of these students have been with me since their Freshmen year. The 2020 class was my first graduating class, so theyve had a special place in my heart.

Its disappointing they missed out on special moments this spring- the van rides, the memories, the pictures, the proms, games, state conferences, concerts, productions, etc. It just sucks. Although I know theyve missed so much, in the last couple months, I hope the memories of the rest of their time at Analy and in ANX 3 will override what was missed. Class of 2020, you are one for the books & I love you all!

A special thank you to the Sebastopol Ag Boosters for having the signs made for each program completer. Thank you Brenda Hawkes Ficco for doing an amazing job with them, and thank you Jennifer Marcussen for helping me get the stoles just in time! It takes a village!

post_text: Congratulations!!
shared_text:
El Mo Ed Fund
May 14 at 6:04 AM 路

We're so proud of you, Adyson Posner, for winning The Press Democrat's 2020 Youth Service Award for Health Science. The Press Democrat said:

"Authentic and humble, this nominee has committed the last three years to being a volunteer Peer Educator at the Forestville Teen Clinic.

"Her volunteer work includes; working in laboratory processing, patient charts, data management, community outreach, public speaking and sex education.

"She has always been a shy person, and credits her volunteerism for her growth. Through her work she has grown to understand the importance of community. She quoted, 'healthcare is about more than just ones physical health,' and acknowledged that sexual health, building healthy relationships and safety are all integral parts of a persons health.

"Because of her involvement in many aspects of healthcare, the award goes to Adyson Posner from El Molino High School." Read more here: https://www.pressdemocrat.com/lifestyle/10959108-181/meet-this-years-winners-of

post_text:
Congratulations John Baseman, EMHS Senior
#westcountypride
shared_text:
El Molino High School
April 23 at 7:31 PM 路

Senior Spotlight!
John Baseman

What is your favorite high school memory?
My favorite memory at El Molino has been playing sports with my friends.


Who is your favorite teacher?
I Like all my teachers but I Think I would have to say Coach Roan is my favorite.


What is your favorite Covid 19 Activity?
My favorite covid 19 activity is skateboarding around my neighborhood.


What have you accomplished during the shelter in place that you normally wouldn't have?
Something I accomplished that I wouldn't normally have is reading a book for fun and to enjoy it.


What three things can you NOT live without?
Three things that I can't live without are my family/friends, music, and sports/outdoor activities.
娥

Congrats Jack!もわ

History Matters: Fireside chat wisdom

John Grech recalls the effective leadership of Franklin Roosevelt.

With politics these days as divisive as they are amid this crisis, it seems on a national level we are lacking a voice of stability and comfort  one that Americans clearly had during the Great Depression, a crisis that lasted a decade and ruined millions of lives.

post_text: A tribute to senior Colman Hayes
shared_text:
El Mo Ed Fund
April 22 at 9:59 PM 路

A tribute to senior Colman Hayes

El Molinos Colman Hayes was among the top athletes of his graduating class, excelling on football, wrestling and track teams. There were few better on the gridiron, where he was a fierce, all-league linebacker who led the Lions in tackles for two seasons. In addition to three years on the El Mo wrestling team, Hayes enjoyed success in track and field, where he was among the teams best shot put and discus throwers and a North Coast Section qualifier.

See the story here: http://www.sonomawest.com/sonoma_west_times_and_news/sports/tribute-to-graduating-senior-student-athletes/article_d4e2e5dc-84c9-11ea-ba28-33bb8f480bef.html

shared_text:
El Molino High School
April 22 at 4:39 PM 路

Senior Spotlight!
Richard Luoto

What is your favorite high school memory?
Performing Laramie Project my sophomore year because it allowed me to explore characters that were incredibly different from anything I had done before or since. Every night when we finished, you could see the tears in the eyes of every audience member. Knowing we changed people every performance was magical.


Who is your favorite teacher?
Newly-knighted Sir John Grech and Jolene Johnson.


What is your favorite Covid 19 Activity?
Attempting to learn piano, cooking, and virtual vocal lessons.


What have you accomplished during the shelter in place that you normally wouldn't have?
Ive finished two books which is pretty big considering I never had time, and baking challah successfully three times!


What three things can you NOT live without?
Music, Netflix, and my friends.
娥吼

Congrats Ricky!もわ

shared_text:
El Molino High School is in Forestville, California.
April 6 at 12:18 PM 路 Forestville, CA 路

Class of 2020
We miss you. We love you. We honor you. We know this is a hard time for all of our students, but especially for our graduating seniors.
We know that you will all go on to do big and great things and represent El Molino well.
We are so proud of the young people that you are and we cannot wait to celebrate with you soon. Keep up the good work, finish strong and we will soon be together to celebrate your years at El Molino.
#classof2020 #golions #elmoyouknow @ Forestville, California

post_text: AP information
shared_text:
The College Board
March 20 at 10:24 AM 路

We know the coronavirus has created challenges for AP students and teachers. Heres how the College Board will support you during this time:

1锔 Were providing free, live and on-demand AP courses

To support AP students affected by school closures due to COVID-19, students and schools will have access to live AP review lessons, delivered by AP teachers from across the country. Lessons will begin March 25.

2锔 Were developing a new at-home testing option

Because of the challenges created by COVID-19, were developing a new at-home AP Exam option. Students will be able to test on a computer, tablet, or smartphone.

We will invest so that every AP student impacted by COVID-19 has the tools and connectivity they need to review AP content online and take the exam from home.

During this challenging time, we will work to give every AP student the opportunity to earn the college credit and placement theyve been working toward all year while maintaining a focus on the health and safety of our AP community.

More details here: http://spr.ly/61851tbn3.

On behalf of Band Director Casey Jones, the students of the Analy High School Music Program and the Board of the Analy Band Wagon, we would like to express our deepest gratitude to Sebastopol Safeway Store Manager, Heath Abreu and the Safeway Foundation for their generous grant of $1,500 to Analy Band Wagon. These funds will be used to support our student musicians, Analys music curriculum and our continuing pursuit of excellence for this outstanding program.

We are honored to be selected for this grant and to be part of the Regrand Opening of Sebastopol Safeway!

Congratulations Analy Band Program!
